Cell[TextData[{
 "\tLet us simulate the experiment of making this investment 200 times, and \
keep track of the investor's profit under the optimal choice ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["q", "*"], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", and then under a less than optimal choice.  This will give us numerical \
evidence that this borrowing is a good thing for the investor.  We will plot \
a histogram, and compute a sample mean and standard deviation of profit in \
each case.  The distribution of the stock rate of return will be assumed \
normal.  The rate of return information will be as described in the problem, \
and we will take an initial $100 investment and an investor with risk \
aversion parameter ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"a", "=", "10"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ".  First we define a simulator of total returns given initial wealth ",
 StyleBox["W",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", portfolio coefficient ",
 StyleBox["q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", the rates of return ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "1"], TraditionalForm]]],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Mu]", "2"], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", the standard deviation of the stock return ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "2"], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", and the number of simulations desired."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.438722942267*^9, 3.4387229428970003`*^9}}],

