Cell[TextData[{
 "Our second problem is the option pricing problem.  An asset called a ",
 StyleBox["call option of European type",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " can be purchased, which is a contract that gives its owner the right to \
buy a share (actually, it is more commonly 100 shares) of another risky asset \
at a fixed price ",
 StyleBox["E",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " per share at a particular time ",
 StyleBox["T",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " in the future.  The price ",
 StyleBox["E",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is called the ",
 StyleBox["exercise price",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " of the option.  The question is, what is the present value of such a call \
option contract?  (The \"European\" designation means that it is not possible \
to exercise the option until time ",
 StyleBox["T",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", while options of ",
 StyleBox["American type",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " permit the option to be exercised at any time up to ",
 StyleBox["T",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". )\n\tThe value of the European call option depends on how the risky \
asset, whose price at time ",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " we denote by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"P", "(", "t", ")"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", moves in time.  If the final price ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"P", "(", "T", ")"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 " exceeds ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["E", TraditionalForm]]],
 ", the owner of the option can exercise it, buy the share at price ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["E", TraditionalForm]]],
 ", then immediately resell it at the higher price ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"P", "(", "T", ")"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 " for a profit of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"P", "(", "T", ")"}], "-", "E"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ".  But if ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"P", "(", "T", ")"}], "<", "E"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 " then it does not pay to exercise the option to buy, so the option becomes \
valueless.  \n\tSuppose that the value of money discounts by a percentage of ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " per time period.  This means that a dollar now is worth ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"1", "+", "r"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 " times the worth of a dollar next time period; equivalently a dollar in the \
next time period is worth only ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"1", "+", "r"}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]]],
 " times a dollar in present value terms.  Similarly, a dollar at time ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["T", TraditionalForm]]],
 " is only worth ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"1", "+", "r"}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"-", "T"}]], TraditionalForm]]],
 " times a dollar now.  Therefore, the present value of the call option is \
the expectation"
}], "Text",
