Cell[TextData[{
 "\tIt appears that formula (10) solves the option valuation problem, but \
there is a little more to the story.  Economic restrictions against the \
ability of investors to arbitrage, i.e., to earn unlimited risk-free returns \
at rates above the standard risk-free rate ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", imply that we may assume not only that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"a", "<", "r", "<", "b"}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", but also that"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.438603039122324*^9, 3.438603039125324*^9}}],

